<headline>Special Weather Statement issued December 26 at 12:07AM EST  by NWS Albany</headline>
<description>...PATCHY FREEZING RAIN POSSIBLE OVERNIGHT...
Precipitation will taper off from west to east through 3 AM.
Until then, patchy freezing rain is possible in some spots where
temperatures are hovering around 32 degrees. This could result in
some slippery spots on untreated roads and walking surfaces. Use
caution if out and about overnight.</description>
